{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-ryan-increasingly-at-odds-over-future-of-the-gop/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Donald Trump wants to win the White House in the fall. Paul Ryan wants to save his vision of the Republican Party for years to come. ", "date": "2016-03-29 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/bernie-sanderss-three-state-sweep-doesnt-resolve-delegate-math-problem/", "text": "Sen. Bernie Sanders made a sweep of three states in primary contests over the weekend. Amy Walter of The Cook Political Report and NPR\u2019s Tamara Keith join Gwen Ifill to discuss why Sanders has a \u201cmath problem\u201d despite his wins, Hillary Clinton\u2019s enthusiasm gap among younger voters, the GOP\u2019s war of words over wives and whether Donald Trump is making headway with the Republican establishment. ", "date": "2016-03-28 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/clinton-americans-should-put-court-nomination-at-forefront/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Hillary Clinton wants voters to consider what Republican front-runner Donald Trump might do to shape the Supreme Court. ", "date": "2016-03-28 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/call-to-arms-or-satire-petition-pleads-for-open-carry-at-gop-convention/", "text": "A petition seeking to allow firearms to be openly carried inside the arena for this summer\u2019s Republican National Convention is sparking debate, attracting tens of thousands of signatures in a matter of days. But is it for real? And who actually started it? ", "date": "2016-03-28 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/mock-trump-tombstone-removed-from-nycs-central-park/", "text": "NEW YORK \u2014 A mock tombstone for Donald Trump has been removed from New York City\u2019s Central Park. ", "date": "2016-03-28 00:00:00"}
