{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trumps-penchant-for-phone-interviews-draws-network-ire/", "text": "In television news, a telephone interview is typically frowned upon. Donald Trump\u2019s fondness for them is changing habits and causing consternation in newsrooms, while challenging political traditions. ", "date": "2016-03-27 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/could-anti-trump-protesters-propel-his-candidacy-forward/", "text": "As demonstrators escalate their tactics, they also risk helping Trump, especially among Republican voters his rivals are furiously trying to persuade to reject the billionaire businessman. ", "date": "2016-03-26 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/black-women-uniting-in-support-for-clinton-in-2016/", "text": "Black women, part of President Barack Obama\u2019s winning coalition in 2008 and 2012, have locked arms behind Clinton, hailing her as a Democratic standard-bearer, survivor and friend. ", "date": "2016-03-26 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-under-fire-for-jabs-aimed-at-cruzs-wife/", "text": "Donald Trump\u2019s latest rude comments about Ted Cruz\u2019s wife are raising new alarms among Republicans about the party front-runner\u2019s ability to win over women, especially in a potential fall presidential match-up with Hillary Clinton. ", "date": "2016-03-26 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/sanders-seeking-caucus-wins-in-hawaii-alaska-and-washington/", "text": "Bernie Sanders scored three wins in Western caucus contests, giving a powerful psychological boost to his supporters but doing little to move him closer to securing the Democratic nomination. ", "date": "2016-03-26 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/reid-predicts-senate-will-confirm-garland-after-clinton-win/", "text": "LAS VEGAS \u2014 Senate Minority Leader Harry Reid predicts the Senate will confirm Merrick Garland for the Supreme Court after Hillary Clinton wins the presidential election in November. ", "date": "2016-03-25 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/cruz-says-trump-stoking-false-rumors-about-his-wife/", "text": "OSHKOSH, Wisconsin \u2014 Ted Cruz accused Republican presidential rival Donald Trump of stoking false rumors about his personal life on Friday, charging that the billionaire businessman and GOP front-runner was trafficking in \u201csleaze\u201d and \u201cslime.\u201d ", "date": "2016-03-25 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/arizona-democrats-protest-long-poll-wait-for-primary-voting/", "text": "PHOENIX \u2014 Hours-long waits for some Arizona residents for presidential primary voting have led to accusations of voter suppression from Democrats and civil rights proponents who cite a decision by elections officials to slash the number of polling places this \u2026 ", "date": "2016-03-25 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/why-economic-anxiety-is-driving-working-class-voters-to-trumpism/", "text": "Economic anxiety has taken center stage in this year\u2019s election, driving many angry voters to rally  behind Donald Trump. According to conservative Charles Murray, this anxiety can be traced back to deep-seated feelings of marginalization among working class families, exacerbated by the perceived disconnect between themselves and the political elite. Economics correspondent Paul Solman reports. ", "date": "2016-03-24 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/cruz-calls-trump-a-sniveling-coward/", "text": "DANE, Wis. \u2014 Ted Cruz branded Donald Trump a \u201csniveling coward\u201d Thursday as the feud between the Republican presidential contenders over their wives took a nastier turn. ", "date": "2016-03-24 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/are-there-echoes-of-george-wallace-in-trumps-message/", "text": "One presidential candidate pledged to \u201cStand up for America.\u201d Two generations later, another promises to \u201cMake America Great Again.\u201d Their common denominator: convincing certain Americans that their version of the United States is under threat. ", "date": "2016-03-24 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/bernie-sanderss-plan-to-destroy-isis/", "text": "Democratic presidential candidate Sen. Bernie Sanders joins Judy Woodruff to discuss his approach to rallying Mideast allies to destroy the Islamic State militant group and the path to winning the Democratic nomination despite his delegate deficit. ", "date": "2016-03-23 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/updates/despite-trumps-tight-script-at-aipac-jewish-voters-still-arent-sure/", "text": "Before speaking Monday to the most powerful pro-Israel lobby in the country, the American Israel Public Affairs Committee (or AIPAC), presidential candidate Donald Trump \u2014 who famously says he\u2019s his own best adviser \u2014 sought counsel from Jewish friends and other figures in the community. ", "date": "2016-03-23 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/muslim-americans-show-ted-cruz-their-neighborhoods-on-twitter/", "text": "After Republican presidential candidate Ted Cruz called for police to monitor Muslims on Tuesday, Muslim Americans responded on Twitter by showing images from their everyday lives.  ", "date": "2016-03-23 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/bernie-sanders-breaking-up-banks-is-about-targeting-power-not-just-reducing-risk/", "text": "Judy Woodruff pressed Bernie Sanders on arguments from experts who say federal regulators already have the power to break up the banks, but think the existing system is safer.  ", "date": "2016-03-23 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/ryan-disheartening-politics-risks-distrust-of-government/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 This year\u2019s political campaigns are discouraging and risk alienating people from government and dimming their hopes for the future, House Speaker Paul Ryan says in a speech aiming to describe \u201cwhat politics can be.\u201d ", "date": "2016-03-23 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/jeb-bush-endorses-cruz-for-president/", "text": "Jeb Bush tweeted Wednesday that \u201cTed is a consistent, principled conservative who has shown he can unite the party.\u201d ", "date": "2016-03-23 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/terrorism-looms-as-candidates-compete-in-western-states/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Long lines and high interest marked primary contests in three Western states on Tuesday as Donald Trump and Hillary Clinton fought to extend their delegate leads in a fresh round of voting for would-be commanders in chief. ", "date": "2016-03-22 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-tweets-deletes-reposts-threat-at-cruz/", "text": "Donald Trump apparently has no regrets about making a threat against rival Ted Cruz. ", "date": "2016-03-22 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/updates/the-2016-democratic-race-in-5-questions/", "text": "Today marks exactly 365 days since the starting pistol of the 2016 race, when Texas Senator Ted Cruz became the first in either party to announce a presidential candidacy. Since then the field of hopefuls swelled to 22 and shrunk \u2026 ", "date": "2016-03-22 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/updates/the-2016-gop-race-in-5-questions/", "text": "Today marks exactly 365 days since the starting pistol of the 2016 race, when Texas Senator Ted Cruz became the first in either party to announce a presidential candidacy. Since then the field of hopefuls swelled to 22 and shrunk down to the current set of five. We can\u2019t say we feel nostalgic about the past year of rollicking campaign news, but this unpredictable, eye-opening and important election cycle did make us want to look back a little. And we wondered, what do people remember from the haze and heat so far? And what already has been forgotten? ", "date": "2016-03-22 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/cruz-calls-for-patrol-of-muslim-neighborhoods/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Republican presidential candidate Ted Cruz said Tuesday that surveillance in Muslim neighborhoods in the U.S. must be intensified following the deadly bombings on Brussels\u2019 airport and subway. ", "date": "2016-03-22 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-offers-new-insight-into-foreign-policy-posture/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Confronting doubts about the depth of his knowledge of world affairs, Republican presidential front-runner Donald Trump delivered a sober speech to a pro-Israel crowd, outlining for the first time the team of foreign policy thinkers advising his campaign. ", "date": "2016-03-22 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/cruz-bashes-trump-saying-hes-neutral-on-israel/", "text": "On the heels of Donald Trump\u2019s speech to the American Israel Public Affairs Committee, his political rival Ted Cruz began by calling Trump out on a reference to \u201cPalestine\u201d in his speech. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-calls-iran-biggest-sponsor-of-terrorism-in-aipac-speech/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Republican presidential front-runner Donald Trump is focusing on Iran as he delivers a highly-anticipated foreign policy speech in Washington. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-supporter-arrested-for-punching-protester-at-tucson-rally-is-an-air-force-member/", "text": "TUCSON, Ariz. \u2014 A man captured on video kicking and punching an anti-Donald Trump protester at the presidential candidate\u2019s rally in Tucson on Saturday is a member of the Air Force. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/kasich-tells-aipac-hes-best-qualified-to-lead/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Ohio Gov. John Kasich is stressing his experience as he speaks in front of a major Israel lobby and taking subtle shots at rival Donald Trump. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/donald-trump-unveils-team-of-foreign-policy-advisers/", "text": "Foreign policy dominated the day in the race for the White House. Republican front-runner Donald Trump revealed the first members of his foreign policy team during a trip to Washington, where he met with former House Speaker Newt Gingrich and others to discuss policies and campaign strategy. Meanwhile, Hillary Clinton denounced Trump before pro-Israel group AIPAC. John Yang reports. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/why-most-2016-candidates-are-speaking-at-aipac/", "text": "Tamara Keith of NPR and Stu Rothenberg of the Rothenberg & Gonzales Political Report join Gwen Ifill to discuss the latest in politics, including Hillary Clinton\u2019s remarks to AIPAC, Donald Trump\u2019s meeting with Republicans in Washington, the campaign pivot to the general election race, what to look for in Tuesday\u2019s primary contests and Sen. Elizabeth Warren\u2019s words about Trump on social media. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/sanders-wins-democrats-abroad-global-primary/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Bernie Sanders scored a big win Monday in the Democrats Abroad global primary. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trumps-wall-plan-draws-mixed-reactions-on-the-border/", "text": "NOGALES, Ariz. \u2014 Donald Trump\u2019s ambitious plan to build a giant wall on the border hits close to home for people like Berenice Andrews. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/elizabeth-warren-labels-trump-a-loser-but-also-a-threat/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Sen. Elizabeth Warren labeled Donald Trump a loser, a bully and a threat on Monday, continuing a fierce war of words between the liberal icon and the front-running Republican presidential candidate that has played out on social media and The New York Times. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/clinton-attacks-trumps-qualifications-in-aipac-address/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Hillary Clinton previewed an early line of Democratic attack against Donald Trump on Monday, casting the GOP front-runner as unqualified to handle heated international conflicts as commander in chief in a speech before a prominent pro-Israel advocacy organization. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/pro-israel-policy-conference-nervously-awaits-trump-speech/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 As America\u2019s leading pro-Israel group prepares to hear from nearly all the presidential candidates, most eyes in the audience of thousands will be on GOP front-runner Donald Trump. ", "date": "2016-03-21 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/what-we-can-learn-from-our-history-of-political-discontent/", "text": "A recent poll revealed that only 21 percent of Americans think the country is heading in the right direction. So what happens in a democratic society where understandable grievances have tuned many citizens angry? NewsHour Special Correspondent Jeff Greenfield looks back at a long-ago late winter and two nations that responded in very different ways.  ", "date": "2016-03-20 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/hundreds-rally-against-donald-trump-in-new-york-city/", "text": "Hundreds of protesters gathered in Manhattan on Saturday to rally against the potential candidacy of businessman Donald Trump, the front-runner for the GOP presidential nomination. ", "date": "2016-03-19 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/can-donald-trump-win-over-utahs-mormon-voters/", "text": "Republican presidential front-runner Donald Trump is set to find out whether his brash demeanor will plague him in another Western state with a culture rooted in the Mormon faith that places a high value on manners and amiability. ", "date": "2016-03-19 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/arizona-offers-model-for-how-trump-might-win-the-white-house/", "text": "As Trump looks toward the general election, Arizona shows how conservative populists can thrive even in states with growing minority populations. ", "date": "2016-03-19 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/behind-closed-doors-gop-strategizes-on-how-to-block-trump/", "text": "As Donald Trump approaches the 1,237 pledged delegates who would secure his nomination as the GOP\u2019s presidential candidate, the rifts within the Republican party grow ever deeper. On Thursday, a group of conservative activists met in a closed-door session in Washington, D.C., to discuss how to block Trump\u2019s nomination. \n ", "date": "2016-03-18 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/shields-and-brooks-on-blocking-trump-sanders-chances-and-merrick-garland/", "text": "Judy Woodruff sits down with syndicated columnist Mark Shields and New York Times columnist David Brooks to discuss the week in politics, including how the mainstream GOP can block a Donald Trump nomination, Bernie Sanders\u2019 chances in the western states and Supreme Court nominee Merrick Garland\u2019s contested confirmation. \n ", "date": "2016-03-18 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/romney-to-vote-for-cruz-in-utah-caucuses/", "text": "Former Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney said Friday he will vote for Texas Sen. Ted Cruz in the upcoming caucuses in his home state of Utah, intensifying his attack against front-runner Donald Trump. ", "date": "2016-03-18 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/threatening-letter-sent-to-trump-sons-nyc-home-officials-say/", "text": "NEW YORK \u2014 Police and the FBI are investigating a threatening letter sent to the Manhattan apartment of Donald Trump\u2019s son Eric that contained a white powder, two law enforcement officials said Friday. ", "date": "2016-03-18 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/sanders-says-he-has-a-path-toward-victory-against-clinton/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders says he still maintains a \u201cpath toward victory\u201d in his Democratic presidential bid against Hillary Clinton, rejecting suggestions that she has all but sewn up the party\u2019s nomination. ", "date": "2016-03-18 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/updates/president-trump-for-now-the-world-recoils/", "text": "Foreign ambassadors here in Washington have moved in three months from incredulity to alarm at the prospect of a Donald Trump presidency. \u201cAre American voters really going to choose someone who knows so little about the world, and is so belligerent about it?\u201d one European ambassador asked.  ", "date": "2016-03-18 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/news-wrap-paul-ryan-wont-be-gop-nominee-putin-makes-threat-on-syria/", "text": "In our news wrap Thursday, House Speaker Paul Ryan again denied any possibility that he would stand for the Republican presidential nomination at a contested RNC convention, saying those who argue otherwise should \u201cknock it off.\u201d Also, Russian president Vladimir Putin threatened to send warplanes and troops back into Syria if rebel forces compromise recent government military gains. ", "date": "2016-03-17 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/sanders-concedes-missouri-democratic-primary-clinton-wins/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Bernie Sanders said Thursday he will not seek a recount of results in Missouri\u2019s Democratic presidential primary, conceding defeat to Hillary Clinton. ", "date": "2016-03-17 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/paul-ryan-wants-you-to-know-he-is-not-running-for-president-so-knock-it-off/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 House Speaker Paul Ryan has a message to everyone in the political chattering class who\u2019s speculating that he might emerge as the Republican nominee from a contested convention and save the party from front-runner Donald Trump: \u201cKnock it off.\u201d ", "date": "2016-03-17 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/news-wrap-trump-dismisses-talk-of-contested-convention-fed-maintains-interest-rates/", "text": "In our news wrap Wednesday, Republican frontrunner Donald Trump warned against trying to deny him the party\u2019s presidential nomination via a brokered RNC convention in July. Also, the Federal Reserve decided to hold interest rates steady, saying the U.S. economy is continuing to grow steadily but still faces international risks. \n ", "date": "2016-03-16 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/another-gop-contender-bows-out-can-either-partys-frontrunner-be-stopped/", "text": "Hillary Clinton and Donald Trump scored big victories in Tuesday\u2019s primaries and hold narrow leads in Missouri, where the races have yet to be called. While Sen. Marco Rubio suspended his campaign after losing Florida, Gov. John Kasich was energized by winning Ohio. He and the other challengers soldier on. Judy Woodruff talks to Susan Page of USA Today and Reid Wilson of Morning Consult for more. ", "date": "2016-03-16 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/michelle-obama-tells-sxsw-crowd-she-wont-run-for-president/", "text": "AUSTIN, Texas \u2014 Michelle Obama showed off her vocal chops at the South by Southwest Music Festival but drew a round of disappointed sighs when she told the crowd she has no plans to run for president. ", "date": "2016-03-16 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/ryan-will-not-accept-gop-presidential-nomination-at-contested-convention/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 House Speaker Paul Ryan\u2019s spokeswoman says he \u201cwill not accept a nomination\u201d to be the Republican running for president \u2014 even if his predecessor, John Boehner, nominated him. ", "date": "2016-03-16 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/sanders-needs-big-time-wins-superdelegates-to-catch-clinton/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Bernie Sanders needs some big-time support, fast. ", "date": "2016-03-16 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-not-attending-march-21-debate-in-utah/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 Donald Trump says he will not participate in the next GOP presidential debate on Monday in Utah because \u201cwe\u2019ve had enough debates.\u201d ", "date": "2016-03-16 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/math-and-momentum-point-to-trump-clinton-nominations/", "text": "WASHINGTON \u2014 With math and momentum on his side after more big wins, Republican front-runner Donald Trump called on GOP leaders Wednesday to embrace the public\u2019s \u201ctremendous fervor\u201d for his candidacy. If GOP leaders try to deny him the nomination \u2026 ", "date": "2016-03-16 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/live-blog-super-tuesday-ii-speeches-and-results/", "text": "Call it Mega Tuesday, Super Tuesday II, or any other name, you can follow all of the PBS NewsHour\u2019s election coverage as people in five states and one U.S. territory vote in presidential primaries on March 15. ", "date": "2016-03-15 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/updates/4-important-takeaways-from-tonights-primaries/", "text": "The primary process isn\u2019t over yet, but tonight helped define the race on both sides. Here are a few quick takeaways from Super Tuesday 2. ", "date": "2016-03-15 00:00:00"}
{"url": "http://www.pbs.org/newshour/rundown/trump-tops-rubio-in-florida-falls-to-kasich-in-ohio/", "text": "Donald Trump won a decisive victory in Florida\u2019s primary Tuesday night, forcing home-state Sen. Marco Rubio to abandon the race for the Republican presidential nomination. The brash billionaire also picked up North Carolina and Illinois, but faltered in Ohio. ", "date": "2016-03-15 00:00:00"}
